Uh.

12
00:01:15,916 --> 00:01:18,458
Hold on. What's this?

13
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:20,041
[SUBARU gasps]

14
00:01:20,125 --> 00:01:23,791
[SUBARU]
It's looks like... a bouquet?

15
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:26,791
[NARRATOR] That's right.
Today, September 2nd,

16
00:01:26,875 --> 00:01:30,000
was ace pilot Subaru
Ichinose's 20th birthday.

17
00:01:30,083 --> 00:01:32,166
[SUBARU]
Those sneaky sneak-faces!

18
00:01:32,250 --> 00:01:36,833
That's why they wanted me to
come with them to the Ashigara.

19
00:01:36,916 --> 00:01:39,291
They usually know
to give me my space,

20
00:01:39,375 --> 00:01:42,750
so obviously this is
for a special occasion.

21
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:46,208
[NARRATOR] The Ashigara was a
supply vessel-slash-party barge

22
00:01:46,291 --> 00:01:49,666
equipped with restaurants
and event spaces.

23
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:52,541
[SUBARU] And... done. I've
finished my maintenance,

24
00:01:52,625 --> 00:01:56,083
so I guess I'll just be heading
over to the Ashigara now.

25
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:06,041
[SUBARU] They've clearly
calculated the perfect degree

26
00:02:06,125 --> 00:02:08,875
of surprise-i-tude.
This way, it's still exciting,

27
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:11,583
but I won't get all freaked out
when they spring the trap.

28
00:02:11,666 --> 00:02:13,333
Those guys are the best!

29
00:02:13,416 --> 00:02:14,500
[bell chimes]

30
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:16,500
[CLERK 14A]
Be right with you!

31
00:02:16,583 --> 00:02:18,291
[SUBARU]
This is the perfect spot.

32
00:02:18,375 --> 00:02:20,583
I'll just stand here,
casually reading a comic,

33
00:02:20,666 --> 00:02:22,458
and wait for them to see me.

34
