102
00:06:09,416 --> 00:06:14,416
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

103
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:17,416
[DURANDAL] Let's hear it
for Subaru, everyone.

104
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:25,750
Aw, you shouldn't have!

105
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:28,375
[DURANDAL]
Go on. Blow out the candles.

106
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:29,416
Yeah!

107
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:32,333
[inhales, exhales]

108
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:41,208
God bless us, everyone.

109
00:06:42,041 --> 00:06:45,666
[NARRATOR] Subaru turned 20
and earned his big-boy pants.

110
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:47,958
But with them came the
knowledge that adulthood

111
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:49,875
was a bleak and lonely time.

112
00:06:49,958 --> 00:06:51,916
And that the only people
you can count on

113
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:56,833
to give a crap
about your birthday

114
00:06:56,916 --> 00:07:00,791
are the dysfunctional
weirdos you call family.

